Two prototypes of the CYG-11 seaplane were tested off the coast of Hainan Province in China . 
  The aircraft uses reduced drag and increased lift from the wing-in-ground effect to glide in the sea . 
  It has been developed with Russian engineers and could be used to patrol coastlines . 
  Engineers say the aircraft is capable of flying 62 miles on 28 litres of fuel . 
 